author: stephan
msg: Changed the way pretty printing works.  If pretty print is true then the
class must implement the Printable interface in order to be pretty printed.
This allows child elements to inherit the parents pretty printing state
by default, without affecting elements where white space is significant.
This also fixes the PRE.addElement(Element e) bug jon found.
